<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-05-01T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-05-01T11:00:00-05:00" n="559" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d559">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">611.1631/111: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in El Salvador</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Corrigan</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-05-01T12:00:00-04:00">May 1,
                                1935—noon</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>26. Your despatch 213, April 13. In view of the probability that loan
                            negotiations will be protracted, the Department prefers, unless you
                            perceive strong objections, that you submit Schedule I without further
                            delay.</p>
                        <p>It is hoped that an agreement can be reached in time for presentation to
                            the present Congress in El Salvador.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>